### Events API
### Requires: {{baseUrl}} and {{accessToken}} in http-client env

### List events
GET {{baseUrl}}/events
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Create event (Admin)
# Keep minDeposit in payload because backend still validates/stores it.
POST {{baseUrl}}/events
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "eventName": "Saturday Night",
  "eventDate": "2026-03-21",
  "minDeposit": 0,
  "sectionPricing": {
    "A": 40,
    "B": 50,
    "C": 70,
    "D": 100,
    "E": 250
  },
  "disabledTables": ["A01", "A02"],
  "disabledClients": []
}

###

### Get active event by date
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/by-date/2026-03-21
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Get event by id
# Copy eventId from list/create response
@eventId = 1770859014427-0c47a5de-40f4-4189-96cb-570042451e76
GET {{baseUrl}}/events/{{eventId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Disable event (ACTIVE -> INACTIVE)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/events/{{eventId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "INACTIVE"
}

###

### Re-activate event (INACTIVE -> ACTIVE)
# Returns 409 if another ACTIVE event already holds same date lock.
PUT {{baseUrl}}/events/{{eventId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "ACTIVE"
}

###

### Update disabled tables / clients
PUT {{baseUrl}}/events/{{eventId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "disabledTables": ["A01", "A15"],
  "disabledClients": []
}

###

### Delete event
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/events/{{eventId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
